==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Homoousian
<hw>Ho`mo*ou"si*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/; <?/
the same + <?/ being, essence, substance.]</ety> <fld>(Eccl.
Hist.)</fld> <def>One of those, in the 4th century, who accepted the
Nicene creed, and maintained that the Son had the same essence or
substance with the Father; -- opposed to
<xex>homoiousian</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Homoousian</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Homoousian
<hw>Ho`mo*ou"si*an</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining to the
Homoousians, or to the doctrines they held.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>homophobia</ent>⟦br⟧
